reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best toothbrush ever
reviews.reviewText: I am very sensitive and picky about toothbrushes as I have many dental problems. And this is the toothbrush that makes you excited about toothbrushing time!! It's super soft but dense so it cleans really really thoroughly. I normally brush my teeth with a regular toothbrush first and a single tufted one for second round. With this brush, I don't always need second brushing. It makes me wanna brush my teeth whenever I can! Really!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Curaprox is best manual toothbrush I have tried. Better than Nimbus ultra soft.
reviews.reviewText: I was using an electric toothbrush but noticed my gum in the front teeth was receding probably because I was pressing too hard. I decided to use a manual ultrasoft bristle toothbrush and tried the Nimbus Extra Soft Toothbrushes first. The Nimbus has tapered tips which probably reaches between the gums better than most but I think it is too fine to remove much plaque. The head of the brush is also much larger than the Curaprox so its more difficult to reach in the back of the mouth.The Curaprox cleans very well and leaves my teeth very smooth almost as good as the nano bristle toothbrushes. The problem with the nano bristle toothbrush is that the brush head seems to be too full or bulky so it doesn't clean in between the teeth well. For surface cleaning it can't be beaten but the Curaprox does that and cleans in between as well so for me it's the best I have found so far.

reviews.reviewTitle: Gentle Care for Healthy Smiles: Curaprox CS5460 Ultra Soft Toothbrushes
reviews.reviewText: The Curaprox CS5460 Ultra Soft Toothbrushes have transformed my oral care routine, and I'm excited to award them a perfect five-star rating. These toothbrushes offer a remarkable blend of gentle yet effective cleaning, making them an essential choice for individuals with sensitive teeth and gums.From the very first brush, the quality of the Curaprox CS5460 Ultra Soft Toothbrushes was evident. The toothbrushes' design and ultra-soft bristles reflect the brand's commitment to delivering a comfortable and thorough oral care experience. This ensures that my teeth and gums are cleaned without causing any discomfort.The ultra-soft bristles are a standout feature. These bristles gently clean teeth and massage gums, making them ideal for individuals with sensitivity. The gentle yet effective cleaning action ensures that my oral health is prioritized without any harshness.The pack of three toothbrushes offers practical convenience. With multiple toothbrushes, I can ensure that I always have a fresh brush on hand. This is particularly useful for maintaining oral hygiene and switching brushes after illness.The Curaprox CS5460 toothbrushes are suitable for both men and women, catering to a diverse range of users. The gender-neutral design and effectiveness make them an essential accessory for any bathroom.The brand's commitment to quality is evident in the toothbrushes' construction and design. The bristles are durable and maintain their shape, ensuring a consistent cleaning experience over time.In conclusion, the Curaprox CS5460 Ultra Soft Toothbrushes are a five-star solution for gentle yet effective oral care. Their ultra-soft bristles, convenience, gender-neutral design, quality construction, and sensitivity-friendly benefits make them an essential accessory for individuals with sensitive teeth and gums. Whether you're seeking a comfortable cleaning experience or prioritizing oral hygiene, these toothbrushes are the perfect choice that has earned their five-star rating through their exceptional design and oral care-enhancing benefits.

reviews.reviewText: My dentist told me that my teeth are worn down after several decades of diligent brushing. So I searched for a soft toothbrush and this one is really lovely with dense, soft bristles not hard and scratchy. Feels like I'm brushing my teeth with velvet. It would be good for sensitive teeth. So far, after 6 months use the bristles haven't splayed out like cheap toothbrushes do. Well worth the money.
